				<li id="16704773" class="cmnt-root" data="15" data-d="1654228256000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578133/Sword-of-Night-and-Flame" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">02 Jun 2022 23:50</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16704773" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I must say, I don&apos;t fully understand this sword.<br/><br/>Like, yes, you can grab it early and melt Margit/Godrick with baby&apos;s first Comet Azur but beyond that? It feels kind of weird.<br/><br/>You get this and you level up Int to get a stronk laser beam... But then you&apos;d be better off grabbing the actual Comet Azur as it has longer range and can be continually charged (Making it far more effective with Cerulean Hidden Tear to vaporise whatever target is infront of you)<br/><br/>You level Fth to get a stronk fire slash... But Dragonfire exists which is more flexible (Can be cast while mounted. Can scale off Int with Golden Order Seal. Can be charged to fire off extra times (Which makes it a useful alternative to Comet Azur with Cerulean Hidden Tear for magic resistant enemies). Is by default less FP, has a longer range)<br/><br/>It&apos;s this bizarre combination of using the same stats as the actual spells, to get worse versions of the spells. Unlike, say, Bolt of Granisax which not only gets a better version of a spell (Ancient Lightning Spear &gt; Lightning Spear) but also uses a different stat meaning a Bolt of Granisax build won&apos;t naturally be getting the stats required to cast the actual spell.<br/><br/>With SoNaF&apos;s current stats, it would make more sense if the skills were flipped. If it got an Int based AoE attack (Something similar to Nebula would make sense for a &quot;Night&quot; skill) and the Fth skill was like a fire based Comet Azur. Skills that don&apos;t have direct comparisons in the spell list you&apos;d have access to in an Int/Fth build (The closest you have would be Carian Greatsword and Dragonfire/Agheel&apos;s Fire)</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16704773" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16704773" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>29</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>14</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16704773"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16704773" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16704773"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16704678" class="cmnt-root" data="-5" data-d="1654228219000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578133/Sword-of-Night-and-Flame" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">02 Jun 2022 23:50</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16704678" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I must say, I don&apos;t fully understand this sword.<br/><br/>Like, yes, you can grab it early and melt Margit/Godrick with baby&apos;s first Comet Azur but beyond that? It feels kind of weird.<br/><br/>You get this and you level up Int to get a stronk laser beam... But then you&apos;d be better off grabbing the actual Comet Azur as it has longer range and can be continually charged (Making it far more effective with Cerulean Hidden Tear to vaporise whatever target is infront of you)<br/><br/>You level Fth to get a stronk fire slash... But Dragonfire exists which is more flexible (Can be cast while mounted. Can scale off Int with Golden Order Seal. Can be charged to fire off extra times (Which makes it a useful alternative to Comet Azur with Cerulean Hidden Tear for magic resistant enemies). Is by default less FP, has a longer range)<br/><br/>It&apos;s this bizarre combination of using the same stats as the actual spells, to get worse versions of the spells. Unlike, say, Bolt of Granisax which not only gets a better version of a spell (Ancient Lightning Spear &gt; Lightning Spear) but also uses a different stat meaning a Bolt of Granisax build won&apos;t naturally be getting the stats required to cast the actual spell.<br/><br/>With SoNaF&apos;s current stats, it would make more sense if the skills were flipped. If it got an Int based AoE attack (Something similar to Nebula would make sense for a &quot;Night&quot; skill) and the Fth skill was like a fire based Comet Azur. Skills that don&apos;t have direct comparisons in the spell list you&apos;d have access to in an Int/Fth build (The closest you have would be Carian Greatsword and Dragonfire/Agheel&apos;s Fire)</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16704678" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16704678" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>7</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16704678"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16704678" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16704678"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
